s://CRAN.R-project.org/package=btergm\">btergm</a> - Tools to fit temporal ERGMs by bootstrapped pseudolikelihood. Also provides MCMC maximum likelihood estimation, goodness of fit for ERGMs, TERGMs, and stochastic actor-oriented models (SAOMs), and tools for the micro-level interpretation of ERGMs and TERGMs.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=ergm\">ergm</a> - Estimation of Exponential Random Graph Models (ERGM).\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://mjh4.blogspot.com/2012/09/ergm-edgecov-and-dyadcov-specifications.html\">ERGM: edgecov and dyadcov Specifications</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=GERGM\">GERGM</a> - Estimation and diagnosis of the convergence of Generalized Exponential Random Graph Models (GERGM).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=geomnet\">geomnet</a> - Single-geometry approach to network visualization with ggplot2.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=ggnetwork\">ggnetwork</a> - Multiple-geometries approach to plot network objects with ggplot2.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=hergm\">hergm</a> - Estimate and simulate hierarchical exponential-family random graph models (HERGM) with local dependence.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=hierformR\">hierformR</a> – Determine paths and states that social networks develop over time to form social hierarchies.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=influenceR\">influenceR</a> - Compute various node centrality network measures by Burt, Borgatti and others.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=keyplayer\">keyplayer</a> - Implements several network centrality measures.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=latentnet\">latentnet</a> - Latent position and cluster models for network objects.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=ndtv\">ndtv</a> - Tools to construct animated visualizations of dynamic network data in various formats.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=netdiffuseR\">netdiffuseR</a> - Tools to analyze the network diffusion of innovations.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=network\">network</a> - Basic tools to manipulate relational data in R.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=networkDynamic\">networkDynamic</a> - Support for dynamic, (inter)temporal networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=networksis\">networksis</a> - Tools to simulate bipartite networksgraphs with the degrees of the nodes fixed and specified.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=PAFit\">PAFit</a> - Nonparametric estimation of preferential attachment and node fitness in temporal complex networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=PCIT\">PCIT</a> - Implements Partial Correlation with Information Theory in order to identify meaningful correlations in weighted networks, such as gene co-expression networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=qgraph\">qgraph</a> - Tools to model and visualize psychometric networks; also aimed at weighted graphical models).\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://psychosystems.org/network-model-selection-using-qgraph-1-3-10/\">Network Model Selection Using qgraph 1.3</a> (2014).</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://sachaepskamp.com/qgraph/examples\">qgraph Examples</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.jstatsoft.org/article/view/v048i04\">qgraph: Network Visualizations of Relationships in Psychometric Data</a> (2012).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=relevent\">relevent</a> - Tools to fit relational event models (REM).\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://cran.r-project.org/package=informR\">informR</a> - Tools to create sequence statistics from event lists to be used in <code>relevent</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=rem\">rem</a> - Estimate endogenous network effects in event sequences and fit relational event models (REM), which measure how networks form and evolve over time.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=rgexf\">rgexf</a> - Export network objects from R to GEXF for manipulation with software like Gephi or Sigma.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=sna\">sna</a> - Basic network constructors, measures and visualization tools.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=SocialMediaLab\">SocialMediaLab</a> - Tools for collecting social media data and generating networks from it (<a href=\"http://vosonlab.net/SocialMediaLab\">companion website</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/voson-labSocialMediaLab\">github repo</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=spnet\">spnet</a> - Methods for dealing with spatial social networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=tergm\">tergm</a> - Fit, simulate and diagnose models for temporal exponential-family random graph models (TERGM).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=tnam\">tnam</a> - Tools to fit temporal and cross-sectional network autocorrelation models (TNAM).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=tnet\">tnet</a> - Network measures for weighted, two-mode and longitudinal networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=tsna\">tsna</a> - Tools for temporal social network analysis.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=xergm\">xergm</a> - Extensions of exponential random graph models (ERGM, GERGM, TERGM, TNAM and REM).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:49:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"briatte/awesome-network-analysis","categoryHTML":"<h2>Varia</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://psych-networks.com/tutorial-paper-new-methods-estimating-psychological-networks/\">Tutorial Paper on New Methods for Estimating Psychological Networks</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T09:41:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vert-x3/vertx-awesome","categoryHTML":"<h2>Vert.x Event Bus Clients</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mumez/VerStix\">Smalltalk</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mumez/VerStix\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":9,\"repo\":\"mumez/VerStix\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->- Event bus client for <a href=\"http://pharo.org/\">Pharo Smalltalk</a> using the <a href=\"https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-tcp-eventbus-bridge\">TCP-based protocol</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-tcp-eventbus-bridge\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">45</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":45,\"repo\":\"vert-x3/vertx-tcp-eventbus-bridge\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-14T01:34:48.000Z"},{"awe